#
# chessdb.eco
#
# This is the ECO classification file for ChessDB.
#
# The ChessDB ECO code format allows for extensions: each basic code can have
# a lower case letter (a-z) appended, and a further level (1-4) can be
# added to each extension. So the order of ECO codes for A00 is:
# A00, A00a, A00a1, A00a2, A00a3, A00a4, A00b, A00b1, ..., A00z4.
#
# You can convert this file to PGN format with "eco2pgn" and to EPD
# format with "eco2epd" -- these ChessDB programs are not compiled by
# default so you may need to compile them first, e.g. "make eco2pgn".
#
# Copyright (C) 1999-2003  Shane Hudson (sgh@users.sourceforge.net)
# Created: June 1999.
# Last update: October 2003.
# ChessDB website: http://chessdb.sourceforge.net/

# Many of the B08 lines with ..c6 are reached by the Modern (B06) move order
# with 5...Nf6 -- hence all the lines ending with ...c6 here to catch
